onal name <i>Gerd</i> is a shortened form of   Gerhardt  . Compare   Gardin  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Gardin","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Homero, Ramonda, Ruben.  Italian Mario, Orlando.","Americanized form of German   Gerding  . It is concentrated in NC.","Italian (Veneto): from a pet form of <i>Gardo</i>, a short form of various personal names such as <i>Edgardo</i> and <i>Ildegardo</i>."]},{"name":"Gerhardt","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Armin, Wilhelm, Bernhard, Dieter, Erwin, Gerda, Gerhardt, Heinrich, Heinz, Horst.","German: from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>gēr</i>, <i>gār</i> ‘spear’ + <i>hard</i> ‘hardy, brave, strong’. Compare   Garhart  ,   Gearhart  , and   Gearheart  ."]}]},{"name":"Helena","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Helen  , used also in Germany, the Netherlands, Scandinavia, and Eastern Europe."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Helena Gedding was born about 1324, in Hessett, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, her father, John Gedding, was 35 and her mother, Madam Gedding, was 11322. She married John Bacon III about 1345, in Hessett, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1408, in her hometown, at the age of 85."},"et":{"Abt 1324–1408":"umbes 1324–1408","1324–1408":"1324–1408","1320–1384":"1320–1384","1348–Male":"1348–Surnud","1359–1397":"1359–1397","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","1320–Female":"1320–Surnud","1348":"1348","1359":"1359","1324":"1324","Abt 1397":"umbes 1397","1397":"1397","1320":"1320","about 1345":"umbes 1345","1384":"1384","Abt 1324":"umbes 1324","1408":"1408","1290":"1290","Hessett, Suffolk, England":"Hessett, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bramfield, Suffolk, England":"Bramfield, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bradfield, Norfolk, England":"Bradfield, Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1324